Generic single-database configuration.
Lush Bloom is a command-line application that manages a flower shop's operations, including customer orders, flower inventory, and sales. Built with SQLAlchemy, Alembic, and Python, this project demonstrates real-world database interactions and object-oriented design.

---

 Features

 Manage flowers: Add, view, or remove flowers.
 Handle customers: Register new customers and update their info.
- üßæ Create and manage orders: Link customers to orders and track order items.
 Inventory management: Track available flowers and quantities.
 Database migrations via Alembic.

---

 Tech Stack

- Python 3.8+
- SQLAlchemy (ORM)
- SQLite (Database)
- Alembic (Migrations)
- Typer (CLI Framework)
- Pipenv (Environment management)

